{"title_page": "Dhaka Reporters Unity", "text_new": "{{Infobox organization\n|name         = Dhaka Reporters Unity\n|image        = \n|image_border = \n|size         = \n|alt          = \n|caption      = \n|map          = \n|msize        = \n|malt         = \n|mcaption     = \n|abbreviation = \n|motto        = \n|formation    = 1995\n|extinction   = \n|type         = \n|status       = \n|purpose      = \n|headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]]\n|location     = \n|coords       = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template -->\n|region_served = Bangladesh\n|members  = \n|language     = Bengali\n|leader_title = \n|leader_name  = \n|main_organ   = \n|parent_organization = \n|affiliations = \n|num_staff    = \n|num_volunteers =\n|budget       = \n|website      = [https://www.dru.com.bd/ Dhaka Reporters Unity]\n|remarks      =\n}}\n'''Dhaka Reporters Unity''' ({{Lang-bn|\u09a2\u09be\u0995\u09be \u09b0\u09bf\u09aa\u09cb\u09b0\u09cd\u099f\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u09b8 \u0987\u0989\u09a8\u09bf\u099f\u09bf}}) is a Dhaka-based professional body of reporters.<ref>{{cite news |title=DRU annual election begins |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/politics/dhaka-reporters-unity-dru-annual-election-2019-begins-1833850 |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=The Daily Star |date=30 November 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=\u09a2\u09be\u0995\u09be \u09b0\u09bf\u09aa\u09cb\u09b0\u09cd\u099f\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u09b8 \u0987\u0989\u09a8\u09bf\u099f\u09bf\u09b0 \u09a8\u09c7\u09a4\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09ac\u09c7 \u0986\u099c\u09be\u09a6-\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u099c |url=https://www.dailynayadiganta.com/election/460469/%E0%A6%A2%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE-%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B8-%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%89%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A6-%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BF%E0%A7%9F%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%9C |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=Daily Nayadiganta |language=bn}}</ref> Rafiqul Islam Azad is the President and Reaz Chowdhury is the General Secretary of Dhaka Reporters Unity.<ref>{{cite news |title=Azad Dhaka Reporters Unity president, Reaz general secretary |url=https://www.daily-sun.com/post/442863/Azad-Dhaka-Reporters-Unity-president-Reaz-general-secretary |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=Daily Sun |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nDhaka Reporters Unity was established in 1995 and included reports from both print, electronic media and new organization. The organization has 1800 members. It provide insurance for its members.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dhaka Reporters Unity |url=https://dru.com.bd/Details/page/about-us |website=dru.com.bd |accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> The auditorium at the headquarters of Dhaka Reporters Unity is named after [[Murder of Sagar Sarowar and Meherun Runi|Sagar Sarowar and Meherun Runi]].<ref>{{cite news |title=\u2018Please bring back my father\u2019 |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/city/kidnapping-in-bangladesh-please-bring-back-my-father-1766041 |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=The Daily Star |date=3 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n[[Category:1995 establishments in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Dhaka]]\n[[Category:Trade associations based in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Labour relations in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi journalism organisations]]\n\n\n{{Bangladesh-org-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox organization\n|name         = Dhaka Reporters Unity\n|image        = \n|image_border = \n|size         = \n|alt          = \n|caption      = \n|map          = \n|msize        = \n|malt         = \n|mcaption     = \n|abbreviation = \n|motto        = \n|formation    = 1995\n|extinction   = \n|type         = \n|status       = \n|purpose      = \n|headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]]\n|location     = \n|coords       = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template -->\n