new organization. The organization has 1800 members. It provide insurance for its members.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dhaka Reporters Unity |url=https://dru.com.bd/Details/page/about-us |website=dru.com.bd |accessdate=20 April 2020}}</ref> The auditorium at the headquarters of Dhaka Reporters Unity is named after [[Murder of Sagar Sarowar and Meherun Runi|Sagar Sarowar and Meherun Runi]].<ref>{{cite news |title=\u2018Please bring back my father\u2019 |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/city/kidnapping-in-bangladesh-please-bring-back-my-father-1766041 |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=The Daily Star |date=3 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n[[Category:1995 establishments in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Dhaka]]\n[[Category:Trade associations based in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Labour relations in Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi journalism organisations]]\n{{Bangladesh-org-stub}}\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: Dhaka based \u2192 Dhaka-based", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dhaka_Reporters_Unity"}
{"title_page": "The Courts of Idleness", "text_new": "{{short description|1920 short story collection by Dornford Yates}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books -->\n| name         = The Courts of Idleness\n| image        = The Courts of Idleness, Yates, 1929 printing.jpg\n\n| caption      = 1929 printing\n| author       = [[Dornford Yates]]\n| genre        =\n| publisher    = [[Ward Lock & Co]]<ref name=\"BLcat\">{{Cite web |url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995525&con_lng=eng |title=British Library Item details |website=primocat.bl.uk |access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n| release_date = 1920<ref name=\"BLcat\"/>\n| media_type   = Print \n| pages        = 320<ref name=\"BLcat\"/>\n}}\n\n'''''The Courts of Idleness''''' is a 1920 short story collection by the English author [[Dornford Yates]] (Cecil William Mercer), his second collection.\n\n== Background and plot==\n\nThe book includes two main collections of stories, the first consisting largely of stories written before [[World War I|the war]] and published monthly in [[The Windsor Magazine|''The Windsor Magazine'']] until 1915, with a final story being published in June 1919.{{sfn|Smithers|1982|pp=82, 93}} This ends abruptly when the characters' frivolities are interrupted by a sudden sound which some interpret as a ship's siren and others as the sound of a heavy gun. A moment later, all are killed in the crater of a great shell.{{sfn|Smithers|1982|p=93}} The second collection consists of stories mostly written and published in ''The Windsor Magazine'' after the war;{{sfn|Smithers|1982|p=95}} this returns to the entirely different set of characters from ''[[The Brother of Daphne]].''\n\n== Critical reception ==\n\nThe review in September's [[Punch (magazine)|''Punch'']] was much less enthusiastic than that for the author's first collection, ''[[The Brother of Daphne]]'':{{sfn|Smithers|1982|p=95}} \"The main object of the characters in ''The Courts of Idleness'' ([[Ward Lock & Co|Ward, Lock]]) was to amuse themselves, and as their sprightly conversations were often punctuated by laughter I take it that they succeeded. To give Mr Dornford Yates his due he is expert in light banter; but some three hundred pages of such entertainment tend to create a sense of surfeit.\"<ref name=\"Punch\">{{Cite magazine |date=22 September 1920 |title=Our Booking-Office. (By Mr Punch's Staff of Learned Clerks)|url=http://www.gutenberg.org/files/17653/17653-h/17653-h.htm |magazine=Punch}}</ref> The reviewer ended on a more positive note, saying \"Mr Yates can be strongly recommended to anyone who thinks that the British take themselves too seriously\",<ref name=\"Punch\" /> a quotation that Ward Lock used on the rear covers of many of Yates's later volumes.\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* {{Cite book|ref=harv|title=Dornford Yates |last= Smithers |first=AJ |publisher=[[Hodder & Stoughton|Hodder and Stoughton]] |year=1982 |location=London |isbn=0 340 27547 2}}\n\n[[Category:1920 short story collections]]\n[[Category:Ward Lock & Co books]]\n[[Category:Short story collections by Dornford Yates]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1920 short story collection by Dornford Yates}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2020}}\n{{infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Novels or Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books -->\n| name         = The Courts of Idleness\n| image        = The Courts of Idleness, Yates, 1929 printing.jpg\n\n| caption      = 1929 printing\n| author       = [[Dornford Yates]]\n| genre        =\n| publisher    = [[Ward Lock & Co]]<ref name=\"BLcat\">{{Cite web |url=http://primocat.bl.uk/F?func=direct&local_base=ITEMV&doc_number=003995525&con_lng=eng |title=British Library Item details |website=primocat.bl.uk |access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n| release_date = 1920<ref name=\"BLcat\"/>\n| media_type   = Print \n| pages        = 320<ref name=\"BLcat\"/>\n}}\n\n'''''The Courts of Idleness''''' is a 1920 short story collection by the English author [[Dornford Yates]] (Cecil William Mercer), his second collection.\n\n== Background and plot==\n\nThe book includes two main collections of stories, the first consisting mainly of stories written before [[World War I|the war]] and published monthly in [[The Windsor Magazine|''The Windsor Magazine'']] until 1915, with a final story being published in June 1919.{{sfn|Smithers|1982|pp=82, 93}} This ends abruptly when the characters' frivolities are interrupted by a sudden sound which some interpret as a ship's siren and others as the sound of a heavy gun. A moment later, all are killed in the crater of a great shell.{{sfn|Smithers|1982|p=93}} The second collection consists of stories mostly written and published in ''The Windsor Magazine'' after the war;{{sfn|Smithers|1982|p=95}} this returns to the entirely different set of characters from ''[[The Brother of Daphne]].''\n\n== Critical reception ==\n\nThe review in September's [[Punch (magazine)|''Punch'']] was much less enthusiastic than that for the author's first collection, ''[[The Brother of Daphne]]'':{{sfn|Smithers|1982|p=95}} \"The main object of the characters in ''The Courts of Idleness'' ([[Ward Lock & Co|Ward, Lock]]) was to amuse themselves, and as their sprightly conversations were often punctuated by laughter I take it that they succeeded. To give Mr Dornford Yates his due he is expert in light banter; but some three hundred pages of such entertainment tend to create a sense of surfeit.\"<ref name=\"Punch\">{{Cite magazine |date=22 September 1920 |title=Our Booking-Office. (By Mr Punch's Staff of Learned Clerks)|url=http://www.gutenberg.org/files/17653/17653-h/17653-h.htm |magazine=Punch}}</ref> The reviewer ended on a more positive note, saying \"Mr Yates can be strongly recommended to anyone who thinks that the British take themselves too seriously\",<ref name=\"Punch\" /> a quotation that Ward Lock used on the rear covers of many of Yates's later volumes.\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* {{Cite book|ref=harv|title=Dornford Yates |last= Smithers |first=AJ |publisher=[[Hodder & Stoughton|Hodder and Stoughton]] |year=1982 |location=London |isbn=0 340 27547 2}}\n\n[[Category:1920 short story collections]]\n[[Category:Ward Lock & Co books]]\n[[Category:Short story collections by Dornford Yates]]\n", "name_user": "MichaelMaggs", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBackground and plot:ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Courts_of_Idleness"}
{"title_page": "Daniel Th\u00f8gersen", "text_new": "{{short description|Danish association football player}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Daniel Th\u00f8gersen\n| fullname    = Daniel L\u00f8nborg Th\u00f8gersen\n| image       = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|df=yes|2000|1|8}}\n| birth_place = [[Esbjerg]], Denmark\n| height      = 1.83m\n| position    = [[Defender (association football)|Left back]]<ref>{{WorldFootball.net|daniel-thoegersen}}</ref>\n| currentclub = [[Kolding IF]] (on loan from [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]])\n| clubnumber  = <!-- 33 -->\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Brabrand IF]]\n| youthyears2 = 2012\u20132017\n| youthclubs2 = [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]]\n| years1      = 2017\u2013      \n| clubs1      = [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]] \n| caps1       = 4 \n| goals1      = 0\n| years4      = 2019\n| clubs4      = \u2192 [[N\u00e6stved BK]] (loan)\n| caps4       = 10\n| goals4      = 0\n| years5      = 2020\u2013\n| clubs5      = \u2192 [[Kolding IF]] (loan)\n| caps5       = 0\n| goals5      = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2016\u20132017 \n| nationalteam1  = [[Denmark national under-17 football team|Denmark U17]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 9\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2017\u20132018\n| nationalteam2  = [[Denmark national under-18 football team|Denmark U18]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 5\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2018\u2013 \n| nationalteam3  = [[Denmark national under-19 football team|Denmark U19]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 3\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| pcupdate    = 26 August 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Daniel L\u00f8nborg Th\u00f8gersen''' (born 8 January 2000) is a Danish footballer who plays for [[Danish 1st Division]] club [[Kolding IF]] on loan from [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF Aarhus]].<ref>{{Soccerway|daniel-lonborg-thogersen/463689}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===AGF===\nTh\u00f8gersen started his career at the age of 7 at [[Brabrand IF]], where his father was the coach. At the age of 12, in 2012, Th\u00f8gersen joined [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]].<ref name=ft/> He developed well and was one of the stars of the youth sector, which was rewarded with a youth contract in November 2015.<ref>[https://www.agf.dk/klubben/nyhedsarkiv/2015/september/agf-skriver-kontrakt-med-thoegersen/ AGF SKRIVER KONTRAKT MED TH\u00d8GERSEN], agf.dk, 16 November 2015</ref>\n\nIn the summer 2017, Th\u00f8gersen was permanently promoted into the first team squad and also signed a new three-year professional contract.<ref>[http://www.agf.dk/klubben/nyhedsarkiv/2017/maj/agf-rykker-to-talenter-op-i-a-truppen/ AGF RYKKER TO TALENTER OP I A-TRUPPEN], agf.dk, 18 May 2017</ref> He got his official debut for the club on 29 August 2017 against [[VSK Aarhus]] in the [[Danish Cup]], where he played the whole game.\n\nOn 2 September 2019, the last day of the summer transfer market, Th\u00f8gersen was loaned out to [[Danish 1st Division]] club [[N\u00e6stved BK]] for the rest of 2019 to gain some first team minutes, after having only played six games for AGF.<ref name=ft>[https://www.agf.dk/klubben/nyhedsarkiv/2019/september/daniel-thoegersen-tager-til-naestved/ DANIEL TH\u00d8GERSEN TAGER TIL N\u00c6STVED], agf.dk, 2 September 2019</ref> On 9 December 2019 it was confirmed, that Th\u00f8gersen had been loaned out again, this time to [[Kolding IF]] for the rest of the season.<ref>[https://www.bold.dk/fodbold/nyheder/agf-udlejer-ung-back-til-kolding/ AGF udlejer ung back til Kolding], bold.dk, 9 December 2019</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 28 April 2019}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|Danish Cup\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]]\n|[[2017-18 Danish Superliga|2017\u201318]]\n|Danish Superliga\n|0||0||1||0||1||0\n|-\n|[[2018-19 Danish Superliga|2018\u201319]]\n|Danish Superliga\n|4||0||1||0||5||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!4!!0!!2!!0!!6!!0\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!4!!0!!2!!0!!6!!0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.dbu.dk/landshold/landsholdsdatabasen/PlayerInfo/7648 Daniel Th\u00f8gersen] at DBU\n\n<!-- {{AGF squad}} -->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Th\u00f8gersen, Daniel}}\n[[Category:Danish footballers]]\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Esbjerg]]\n[[Category:Danish Superliga players]]\n[[Category:Danish 1st Division players]]\n[[Category:Aarhus Gymnastikforening players]]\n[[Category:N\u00e6stved BK players]]\n[[Category:Kolding IF players]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Danish association football player}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Daniel Th\u00f8gersen\n| fullname    = Daniel L\u00f8nborg Th\u00f8gersen\n| image       = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|df=yes|2000|1|8}}\n| birth_place = [[Esbjerg]], Denmark\n| height      = 1.83m\n| position    = [[Defender (association football)|Left back]]<ref>{{WorldFootball.net|daniel-thoegersen}}</ref>\n| currentclub = [[Kolding IF]] (on loan from [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]])\n| clubnumber  = <!-- 33 -->\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Brabrand IF]]\n| youthyears2 = 2012\u20132017\n| youthclubs2 = [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]]\n| years1      = 2017\u2013      \n| clubs1      = [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]] \n| caps1       = 4 \n| goals1      = 0\n| years4      = 2019\n| clubs4      = \u2192 [[N\u00e6stved BK]] (loan)\n| caps4       = 10\n| goals4      = 0\n| years5      = 2020\u2013\n| clubs5      = \u2192 [[Kolding IF]] (loan)\n| caps5       = 0\n| goals5      = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2016\u20132017 \n| nationalteam1  = [[Denmark national under-17 football team|Denmark U17]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 9\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2017\u20132018\n| nationalteam2  = [[Denmark national under-18 football team|Denmark U18]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 5\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2018\u2013 \n| nationalteam3  = [[Denmark national under-19 football team|Denmark U19]]\n| nationalcaps3  = 3\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| pcupdate    = 26 August 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Daniel L\u00f8nborg Th\u00f8gersen''' (born 8 January 2000) is a Danish footballer who plays for [[Danish 1st Division]] club [[Kolding IF]] on loan from [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF Aarhus]].<ref>{{Soccerway|daniel-lonborg-thogersen/463689}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===AGF===\nTh\u00f8gersen started his career at the age of 7 at [[Brabrand IF]], where his father was the coach. At the age of 12, in 2012, Th\u00f8gersen joined [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]].<ref name=ft/> He developed well and was one of the stars of the youth sector, which was rewarded with a youth contract in November 2015.<ref>[https://www.agf.dk/klubben/nyhedsarkiv/2015/september/agf-skriver-kontrakt-med-thoegersen/ AGF SKRIVER KONTRAKT MED TH\u00d8GERSEN], agf.dk, 16 November 2015</ref>\n\nIn the summer 2017, Th\u00f8gersen was permanently promoted into the first team squad and also signed a new three-year professional contract.<ref>[http://www.agf.dk/klubben/nyhedsarkiv/2017/maj/agf-rykker-to-talenter-op-i-a-truppen/ AGF RYKKER TO TALENTER OP I A-TRUPPEN], agf.dk, 18 May 2017</ref> He got his official debut for the club on 29 August 2017 against [[VSK Aarhus]] in the [[Danish Cup]], where he played the whole game.\n\nOn 2 September 2019, the last day of the summer transfer market, Th\u00f8gersen was loaned out to [[Danish 1st Division]] club [[N\u00e6stved BK]] for the rest of 2019 to gain some first team minutes, after having only played six games for AGF.<ref name=ft>[https://www.agf.dk/klubben/nyhedsarkiv/2019/september/daniel-thoegersen-tager-til-naestved/ DANIEL TH\u00d8GERSEN TAGER TIL N\u00c6STVED], agf.dk, 2 September 2019</ref> On 9 December 2019 it was confirmed, that Th\u00f8gersen had been loaned out again, this time to [[Kolding IF]] for the rest of the season.<ref>[https://www.bold.dk/fodbold/nyheder/agf-udlejer-ung-back-til-kolding/ AGF udlejer ung back til Kolding], bold.dk, 9 December 2019</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 28 April 2019}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|Danish Cup\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|AGF]]\n|[[2017-18 Danish Superliga|2017\u201318]]\n|Danish Superliga\n|0||0||1||0||1||0\n|-\n|[[2018-19 Danish Superliga|2018\u201319]]\n|Danish Superliga\n|4||0||1||0||5||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!4!!0!!2!!0!!6!!0\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!4!!0!!2!!0!!6!!0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.dbu.dk/landshold/landsholdsdatabasen/PlayerInfo/7648 Daniel Th\u00f8gersen] at DBU\n\n<!-- {{AGF squad}} -->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Th\u00f8gersen, Daniel}}\n[[Category:Danish footballers]]\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Danish Superliga players]]\n[[Category:Danish 1st Division players]]\n[[Category:Aarhus Gymnastikforening players]]\n[[Category:N\u00e6stved BK players]]\n[[Category:Kolding IF players]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n", "name_user": "ArbieP", "label": "safe", "comment": "addedCategory:People from Esbjerg", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daniel_Th%C3%B8gersen"}
{"title_page": "Gansu", "text_new": "{{Short description|Province of China}}\n{{Distinguish|Ginsu}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n| name = {{raise|0.2em|Gansu Province}}\n| native_name = {{lower|0.1em|{{lang|zh|\u7518\u8083\u7701}}}}\n| settlement_type = [[Provinces of China|Province]]\n| translit_lang1 = Name\n| translit_lang1_type = {{nobold|Chinese}}\n| translit_lang1_info = {{lang|zh|\u7518\u8083\u7701}} ({{transl|zh|G\u0101ns\u00f9 Sh\u011bng}})\n| translit_lang1_type1 = {{nobold|Abbreviation}}\n| translit_lang1_info1 = GS / {{linktext|lang=zh|\u7518}} or {{linktext|lang=zh-hans|\u9647}} (pinyin: {{transl|zh|G\u0101n or L\u01d2ng}})\n| image_map = Gansu in China (+all claims hatched).svg\n| mapsize = 275px\n| map_alt = Map showing the location of Gansu Province\n| map_caption = Map showing the location of Gansu Province\n| coordinates = {{Coord|38|N|102|E|type:adm1st|format=dms|display=it}}\n| named_for = {{linktext|lang=zh|\u7518}} {{transl|zh|g\u0101n}}: Ganzhou District, Zhangye <br />{{linktext|lang=zh-hans|\u8083}}/{{lang|zh-hant|\u8085}} {{transl|zh|s\u00f9}}: Suzhou District, Jiuquan\n| seat_type = Capital<br />{{nobold|(and largest city)}}\n| seat = [[Lanzhou]]\n| seat1_type = \n| seat1 = \n| parts_type = Divisions\n| parts_style = para\n| p1 = 14 [[Prefectures of China|prefectures]]\n| p2 = 86 [[Counties of China|counties]]\n| p3 = 1344 [[Townships of China|townships]]\n| leader_title = [[Party Committee Secretary|Secretary]]\n| leader_name = [[Lin Duo]]\n| leader_title1 = Governor\n| leader_name1 = [[Tang Renjian]]\n| area_footnotes = \n| area_total_km2 = 453700\n| area_rank = [[List of Chinese administrative divisions by area|7th]]\n| elevation_max_m = 5830\n| elevation_max_point = \n| elevation_max_ft = \n| elevation_max_rank = \n| elevation_min_m = \n| elevation_min_point = \n| elevation_min_ft = \n| elevation_min_rank = \n| population