tern Time Zone|EST]]\n|team1      = No. 1 [[2019 NJIT Highlanders men's soccer team|NJIT]]\n|score      = 3\u20132\n|aet        = \n|report     = https://asunsports.org/sports/msoc/2019-20/boxscores/20191110_0njb.xml\n|team2      = No. 4 [[2019 Stetson Hatters men's soccer team|Stetson]]\n|goals1     = \n* [[Alejandro Rabell|Rabell]] {{goal|19}}\n* White {{goal|48}}\n* Nino {{yel|64}}\n* Reisgys {{yel|71}}\n* Watkins {{goal|81}}\n|goals2     = \n* McCauley {{yel|15}}\n* Clark {{yel|35}}\n* Scattergood {{goal|49}}\n* Busmann {{yel|80}}\n* Chalbaud {{goal|89}}\n|stadium    = [[J. Malcolm Simon Stadium]]<br>[[Newark, New Jersey]]\n|attendance = 591\n|referee    = Lorant Varga\n}}\n\n=== Final ===\n\n{{Football box\n|date       = November 16\n|time       = 7:00 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n|team1      = No. 1 [[2019 NJIT Highlanders men's soccer team|NJIT]]\n|score      = 2\u20131\n|aet        = \n|report     = https://asunsports.org/sports/msoc/2019-20/boxscores/20191116_wx0b.xml\n|team2      = No. 2 [[2019 Florida Gulf Coast Eagles men's soccer team|FGCU]]\n|goals1     = \n* Nino {{yel|4}}\n* TEAM {{yel|51}}\n* [[Alejandro Rabell|Rabell]] {{goal|70}}\n* Alvarez {{yel|83}}\n* Watkins {{goal|86}}\n|goals2     = \n* Bushey {{goal|45}}\n* Rosales {{yel|52}}\n|stadium    = [[J. Malcolm Simon Stadium]]<br>[[Newark, New Jersey]]\n|attendance = 735\n|referee    = \n}}\n\n== Statistics ==\n=== Top goalscorers ===\n;2 Goals\n* {{flagicon|VEN}} Sebastian Chalbaud \u2013 [[2019 Stetson Hatters men's soccer team|Stetson]]\n* {{flagicon|PUR}} [[Alejandro Rabell]] \u2013 [[2019 NJIT Highlanders men's soccer team|NJIT]]\n* {{flagicon|RSA}} Regsan Watkins \u2013 [[2019 NJIT Highlanders men's soccer team|NJIT]]\n\n;1 Goal\n{{Div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* {{flagicon|CAN}} Brayden Borutskie \u2013 [[2019 Liberty Flames soccer team|Liberty]]\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Zane Bubb \u2013 [[2019 North Florida Ospreys men's soccer team|North Florida]]\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Noah Bushey \u2013 [[2019 Florida Gulf Coast Eagles men's soccer team|FGCU]]\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Chris Degance \u2013 [[2019 Stetson Hatters men's soccer team|Stetson]]\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Miguel DeLeon, Jr. \u2013 [[2019 North Florida Ospreys men's soccer team|North Florida]]\n* {{flagicon|CAN}} O\u2019Vonte Mullings \u2013 [[2019 Florida Gulf Coast Eagles men's soccer team|FGCU]]\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Ivan Rosales \u2013 [[2019 Florida Gulf Coast Eagles men's soccer team|FGCU]]\n* {{flagicon|ENG}} Lewis Scattergood \u2013 [[2019 Stetson Hatters men's soccer team|Stetson]]\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Tyler Welch \u2013 [[2019 Liberty Flames soccer team|Liberty]]\n* {{flagicon|BRB}} Torian Went \u2013 [[2019 North Florida Ospreys men's soccer team|North Florida]]\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Rene White \u2013 [[2019 NJIT Highlanders men's soccer team|NJIT]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== All Tournament Team ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"white-space:nowrap; font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"text-align:center; background:#ddd;\"| '''2019 ASUN Men's Soccer All-Tournament Team'''<ref>{{cite web |title=NJIT Secures First Men's @ASUNSoccer Championship Title |url=https://asunsports.org/sports/msoc/2019-20/releases/20191115o38khu |website=asunsports.org |accessdate=April 20, 2020|date=November 16, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n'''Regsan Watkins''', NJIT<br>\nShak Adams, FGCU<br>\nThomas Delplace, FGCU<br>\nO'Vonte Mullings, FGCU<br>\nIvan Rosales, FGCU<br>\nNoah Gulden, Lipscomb<br>\nBen Locke, Lipscomb<br>\n[[Alejandro Rabell]], NJIT<br>\nThomas Radon, NJIT<br>\nRene White, NJIT<br>\nSebastian Chalbaud, Stetson\n|-\n|<small>MVP in '''Bold'''</small>  \n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://asunsports.org/sports/msoc/championship/2019-20/2019_Championship 2019 ASUN Men's Soccer Championship]\n* [https://asunsports.org/sports/msoc/championship/2019-20/MSOC_Bracket_-_2019.pdf 2019 ASUN Men's Soccer Tournament Bracket]\n\n{{Atlantic Sun Conference men's soccer seasons navbox}}\n{{2019 NCAA Division I men's soccer season}}\n{{2019 in American soccer}}\n\n[[Category:2019 Atlantic Sun Conference men's soccer season|*]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Sun Men's Soccer Tournament]]\n[[Category:2019 in sports in Florida|Atlantic Sun Men's Soccer Tournament]]\n[[Category:2019 in sports in New Jersey|Atlantic Sun Men's Soccer Tournament]]\n[[Category:2019 in sports in Tennessee|Atlantic Sun Men's Soccer Tournament]]\n[[Category:2019 in sports in Virginia|Atlantic Sun Men's Soccer Tournament]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox NCAA Soccer Conference Tournament\n| Year= 2019\n| Conference= Atlantic Sun\n| Division= I\n| Gender= Men's\n| Image= \n| ImageSize=\n| Caption=\n| Teams= 6\n| Matches= 5\n| Attendance=\n| Venue=\n| City=\n| 1stRoundVenue=\n| 1stRoundCity=\n| QuarterVenue= Top two seeds\n| QuarterCity=\n| SemiVenue= Top two seeds\n| SemiCity= \n| FinalVenue= [[J. Malcolm Simon Stadium]]\n| FinalCity= [[Newark, New Jersey]]\n| Champions= [[2019 NJIT Highlanders men's soccer team|NJIT]]\n| TitleCount= 1st\n| Coach= Fernando Barboto\n| CoachCount= 1st\n| MVP= Regsan Watkins\n| MVPTeam= NJIT\n| Broadcast=[[ESPN+]], [[Facebook Live]]\n}}\n{{2019 Atlantic Sun Conference men's soccer standings}}\nThe '''2019 Atlantic Sun Men's Soccer Tournament''', was the 41st edition of the [[Atlantic Sun Men's Soccer Tournament]]. It determined the [[Atlantic Sun Conference]]'s automatic berth for the [[2019 NCAA Division I Men's Soccer Tournament]]. The tournament began on November 8 and concluded on November 16.\n\n[[2019 NJIT Highlanders men's soccer team|NJIT]], the ASUN regular season champions, won the tournament for the first time in program history. They defeated [[2019 Florida Gulf Coast Eagles men's soccer team|Florida Gulf Coast]] in the finals, 2\u20131.<ref>{{cite web |title=Men's Soccer Captures First ASUN Conference Tournament Title|url=https://news.njit.edu/mens-soccer-captures-first-asun-conference-tournament-title|website=njit.edu|publisher=NJIT News|accessdate=April 20, 2020|date=November 17, 2019}}</ref> NJIT earned their first-ever berth to the NCAA Tournament, where they were defeated in the first round by [[2019 Providence Friars men's soccer team|Providence]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Scandura|first1=Mike|title=PC men\u2019s soccer team beats NJIT, 2-0, advances to 2nd round|url=https://www.providencejournal.com/sports/20191121/pc-mens-soccer-team-beats-njit-2-0-advances-to-2nd-round|website=providencejournal.com|publisher=[[The Providence Journal]] |accessdate=April 20, 2020|date=November 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Seeds ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!Seed\n!School\n!Conference\n!Tiebreaker\n|-\n! 1\n|NJIT\n|5\u20131\u20130\n|\n|-\n! 2\n|Florida Gulf Coast\n|4\u20131\u20131\n|\n|-\n! 3\n|North Florida\n|3\u20132\u20131\n|UNF 2\u20131 vs. STET\n|-\n! 4\n|Stetson\n|3\u20132\u20131\n|STET 1\u20132 vs. UNF\n|-\n! 5\n|Lipscomb\n|3\u20133\u20130\n|\n|-\n! 6\n|Liberty\n|1\u20135\u20130\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n== Bracket ==\n\n{{6TeamBracket \n| RD1= First round<br>Nov. 8\n| RD2= Semifinals<br>Nov. 10\n| RD3= Final<br>Nov. 16\n| group1=\n| group2=\n\n| RD1-seed1= 4\n| RD1-team1= '''[[2019 Stetson Hatters men's soccer team|Stetson]]'''\n| RD1-score1= '''2'''\n| RD1-seed2= 5\n| RD1-team2= [[2019 Lipscomb Bisons men's soccer team|Lipscomb]]\n| RD1-score2= 1\n\n| RD1-seed3= 3\n| RD1-team3= '''[[2019 North Florida Ospreys men's soccer team|North Florida]]''' ([[Overtime (sports)|OT]])\n| RD1-score3= '''3'''\n| RD1-seed4= 6\n| RD1-team4= [[2019 Liberty Flames soccer team|Liberty]]\n| RD1-score4= 2\n\n| RD2-seed1= 1\n| RD2-team1= '''[[2019 NJIT Highlanders men's soccer team|NJIT]]'''\n| RD2-score1= '''3'''\n| RD2-seed2= 4\n| RD2-team2= [[2019 Stetson Hatters men's soccer team|Stetson]]\n| RD2-score2= 2\n\n| RD2-seed3= 2\n| RD2-team3= '''[[2019 Florida Gulf Coast Eagles men's soccer team|FGCU]]'''\n| RD2-score3= '''2'''\n| RD2-seed4= 3\n| RD2-team4= [[2019 North Florida Ospreys men's soccer team|North Florida]]\n| RD2-score4= 1